                            <comment id="17570368" author="pkarwasz" created="Sat, 23 Jul 2022 20:19:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=twisterrob&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;twisterrob&quot;&gt;twisterrob&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you for reporting the issue. The problem you are having is not with the &lt;tt&gt;highlight&lt;/tt&gt; pattern, but the &lt;tt&gt;style&lt;/tt&gt; pattern:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the &lt;tt&gt;highlight&lt;/tt&gt; pattern separates the keywords with white space: e.g. &quot;&lt;tt&gt;INFO=bright white&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;,&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the &lt;tt&gt;style&lt;/tt&gt; pattern separates the keywords with commas: e.g. &quot;&lt;tt&gt;bright, white&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I agree that this is inconsistent, but it is easily fixable: instead of just using commas as separators in the &lt;tt&gt;style&lt;/tt&gt; pattern, we can use commas &lt;b&gt;or&lt;/b&gt; white space. This way we take care of backward compatibility and bring some consistency to the two patterns. Can you open a new JIRA ticket for this and perhaps submit a PR?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17570374" author="twisterrob" created="Sat, 23 Jul 2022 21:14:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh, thanks for clearing it up. I thought it was the same as this ticket dealt with colors &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; I raised &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-3561&quot; title=&quot;Ansi color with spaces in style pattern not supported&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LOG4J2-3561&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LOG4J2-3561&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I won&apos;t be able to work on it though.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
